===============================================================================
HUMANITARIAN CONTEXT
===============================================================================

MedSupply Relay is part of a humanitarian open source initiative.

The project was created to support emergency logistics and information
coordination where hospitals, shelters, volunteers, donors, medical teams,
and affected communities may have unstable or unavailable internet access.

Medicine supply may exist in one location while an urgent demand exists in
another location.

The purpose of the project is to reduce the information gap between those
points.

The application is intentionally focused on a narrow emergency workflow:

1. Register available medicine supply.
2. Register urgent medicine demand.
3. Continue registering information while offline.
4. Synchronize records when connectivity becomes available.
5. Review compatible supply and demand matches.
6. Reserve available stock before pickup.
7. Track medicine movement through the operational reservation flow.
8. Support contingency coordination through TXT and CSV exports.

The project is not intended to become a full hospital management platform.

In an emergency, simplicity is a feature.

===============================================================================
OFFLINE-FIRST PURPOSE
===============================================================================

The MedSupply Relay PWA is designed to allow emergency users to continue
recording essential information when internet connectivity is unavailable.

Local application data may include:

- relief locations;
- medicine supply items;
- medicine demand items;
- synchronization batches;
- synchronization logs.

When connectivity and the MedSupply Relay API become available, pending local
records may be synchronized with the backend.

Real shared-stock reservations require backend availability because a
reservation affects stock availability shared between operational teams.

===============================================================================
MVP OPERATIONAL FLOW
===============================================================================

Supply registration:

Shelters, warehouses, collection points, donors, NGOs, mobile units, and
support teams may register available medicines and supplies.

Demand registration:

Hospitals, medical posts, shelters, mobile medical units, and emergency teams
may register urgent medicine demands.

Offline mode:

Users may continue recording essential supply and demand information without
an active API connection.

Synchronization:

Pending records may be sent to the MedSupply Relay backend when connectivity
returns.

Matching:

The system may display compatible opportunities between open medicine demand
and available medicine supply.

Reservation:

Operational teams may reserve currently free stock before pickup to reduce
double allocation.

The normal reservation workflow is:

Pending -> Confirmed -> In Transit -> Delivered

Contingency export:

Coordination teams may access TXT and CSV match exports for low-infrastructure
operational communication.

===============================================================================
ORIGINAL MVP ACCEPTANCE PRINCIPLE
===============================================================================

A simplified representation of the original operational objective is:

If Hospital Y needs Paracetamol
and Shelter X has compatible available Paracetamol,
then the system should be capable of presenting a compatible supply and
demand opportunity between those locations.

The current implementation includes additional stock, unit, status,
reservation, quantity, priority, and compatibility rules.

